55
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:35,840
The 1,500-meter race is in its last phase now.

56
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:37,189
Lu Ming Yang of Class 5 Year 11

57
00:05:37,190 --> 00:05:39,820
still has the lead.
[South Lake City No. 3 High School's twenty-fifth Sports Day]

58
00:05:39,820 --> 00:05:41,599
This is an encouraging message

59
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:44,770
from Class 5 Year 11.

60
00:05:44,770 --> 00:05:47,440
I can't eat anymore.

61
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:49,869
I thought you just had a meal with No. 3 High School's coach?

62
00:05:49,870 --> 00:05:50,599
Aren't you full?

63
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,159
We were busy discussing the talents here.

64
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:54,410
I didn't manage to eat much. Let's go.

65
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:56,500
Liu!

66
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:57,239
Director Wang!

67
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:59,320
- You're here?
- Come on.

68
00:05:59,320 --> 00:06:00,069
Nice to meet you.

69
00:06:00,070 --> 00:06:00,949
Let me introduce you.

70
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:01,999
This is my teaching assistant, Xiao Luo,

71
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,069
- a postgraduate student in Athletic Training.
- Nice to meet you.

72
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:04,830
Welcome.

73
00:06:05,955 --> 00:06:07,510
They're quite good, right?

74
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:08,190
Quite good.
[Wang Qi Lin: Head of South Lake University Sports Dept.]

75
00:06:08,191 --> 00:06:08,830
[Luo Na: assistant coach, South Lake University postgrad]

76
00:06:08,831 --> 00:06:10,479
Then recruit more of them this year.

77
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,949
Give the children opportunities.

78
00:06:11,950 --> 00:06:13,720
Don't worry.

79
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:17,159
Let's look forward
[Duan Yu Cheng, South Lake City No. 3 High School]

80
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:18,479
to their performances

81
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:20,160
and see who will be the winner.

82
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:23,930
Athletes, make your classes proud.

83
00:06:23,930 --> 00:06:26,599
We came here mainly to check out

84
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,450
talents in high jump.

85
00:06:28,450 --> 00:06:29,429
They did great

86
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:31,429
in the municipal sports competition.

87
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:33,530
Their physiques are quite good too.

88
00:06:34,650 --> 00:06:40,690
You can do it!

89
00:06:40,690 --> 00:06:42,560
Keep an eye on them.

90
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:03,620
[Four hundred meters, Duan Yu Cheng]

91
00:07:11,430 --> 00:07:13,460
On your marks!

92
00:07:19,150 --> 00:07:22,090
[With your hard work, you will be the champion.]

93
00:07:26,070 --> 00:07:28,190
Get set!

94
00:07:34,270 --> 00:07:37,269
With their classmates' anticipation,

95
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:39,930
the athletes flew down the race track.

96
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:44,500
Each of them looks valiant and energetic.

97
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:47,620
They run forward with all they have.

98
00:07:47,620 --> 00:07:50,429
The athlete on the third track from Class 2 Year 12,

99
00:07:50,430 --> 00:07:53,559
Duan Yu Cheng, has overtaken the others

100
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,359
and taken the lead.

101
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:57,679
He's fighting with the other two athletes

102
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,829
beside him for the final victory.

103
00:07:59,830 --> 00:08:02,230
The finish line is right in front of them.

104
00:08:02,230 --> 00:08:05,520
Athletes, you can do it!

105
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:11,430
You can do it!

106
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:19,390
Hooray!

107
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:49,200
An excellent athlete

108
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:52,190
must radiate positive energy.

109
00:08:52,190 --> 00:08:55,200
He has to be proactive, optimistic,

110
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:57,650
and determined.

111
00:08:58,140 --> 00:09:00,079
Even if he's at his lowest moment,

112
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:03,070
he has to radiate energy.

113
00:09:03,070 --> 00:09:05,360
When you look at

114
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:07,960
an outstanding athlete,

115
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:13,550
it's as if you're looking at the sun.

116
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:26,600
"When you look at him, it's as if you're looking at the sun."

117
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,509
The third lane athlete

118
00:09:30,510 --> 00:09:32,149
doesn't seem to belong in this event.

119
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:33,810
Let me check.

120
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:36,790
Is he the one?

121
00:09:37,390 --> 00:09:38,850
Duan Yu Cheng,
[Name]

122
00:09:38,850 --> 00:09:40,789
1.79 meters.
[Height: 179 cm (5'10")]

123
00:09:40,790 --> 00:09:42,950
His specialty is high jump.
[Track and Field: High Jump]

124
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:43,959
You can do it.

125
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:46,239
[Duan Yu Cheng]

126
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:48,389
All athletes in the high jump event,

127
00:09:48,390 --> 00:09:50,680
please report to check-in at once.

128
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:53,520
His height is okay

129
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,560
among ordinary people.

130
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:57,560
If he truly wishes to be an athlete,

131
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:58,869
at most, he can go for long jump.

132
00:09:58,870 --> 00:10:00,079
High jump?

133
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:02,590
There's no way he'll make it.

134
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:06,600
Wait...

135
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:09,720
Liu Shan seems like a better candidate.

136
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,959
Let's go. Let's check him out.

137
00:10:12,959 --> 00:10:14,800
Xiao Liu, I'll go and check him out.

138
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,170
Go ahead, Director Wang. Let's keep in touch.

139
00:10:16,170 --> 00:10:16,980
All right.

140
00:10:16,980 --> 00:10:18,550
I appreciate your effort.

141
00:10:19,150 --> 00:10:21,770
Duan Yu Cheng, you can do it!

142
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,269
Duan Yu Cheng, you can do it!

143
00:10:35,270 --> 00:10:37,490
Go for it!

144
00:10:37,990 --> 00:10:39,750
[Duan Yu Cheng, South Lake City No. 3 High School]

145
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:45,420
Duan Yu Cheng!

146
00:10:45,420 --> 00:10:47,420
Excuse me!

147
00:10:47,420 --> 00:10:48,959
I thought you went for the 100-meter sprint.

148
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:50,610
What are you doing in my event?

149
00:10:50,610 --> 00:10:52,199
What do you mean by "your event"?

150
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,509
The 100-meter sprint finals won't start soon.

151
00:10:53,510 --> 00:10:55,439
I can join them after I defeat you.

152
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:57,250
Defeat me?

153
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:59,570
Are you still dreaming?

154
00:11:00,550 --> 00:11:02,180
Loser,

155
00:11:02,180 --> 00:11:03,669
is blind optimism all you have left

156
00:11:03,670 --> 00:11:06,490
after losing to me a long time ago?

157
00:11:06,490 --> 00:11:08,170
It's good. Keep it up.

158
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:09,149
Listen up.

159
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:11,490
Duan Yu Cheng, you're so handsome!

160
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:17,560
What's up with the chanting?

161
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:19,070
Do they think you can win by good looks?

162
00:11:19,070 --> 00:11:20,999
I can defeat you with my solid skill.

163
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,980
But it's not bad to be popular with girls.

164
00:11:22,980 --> 00:11:25,119
- That’s right!
- That’s right!

165
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:28,540
You should jot it down if you think I'm right.

166
00:11:30,030 --> 00:11:31,640
You're always right.

167
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,740
Am I right, Shorty?

168
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:34,580
Hey!

169
00:11:34,580 --> 00:11:36,820
Horse Face, don't make personal attacks.

170
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:39,719
You can't beat me in a 100-meter race.

171
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:40,549
What's wrong with the 100-meter race?

172
00:11:40,550 --> 00:11:42,199
Do you think you can run fast?

173
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:44,350
Don't let me catch you!

174
00:11:53,670 --> 00:11:55,490
No. 1032,

175
00:11:55,490 --> 00:11:59,000
prepare for your first attempt at 1.85 meters.

176
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:01,199
No. 1039, get ready.

177
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,720
Duan Yu Cheng, you can do it!

178
00:12:03,550 --> 00:12:05,840
You should give up when you're this short.

179
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:08,080
Just accept your destiny.

180
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:22,960
Duan Yu Cheng, you can do it!

181
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:32,020
Stefan Holm (Swedish high jumper).

182
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,770
You know him, too?

183
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:42,930
Your fourth step was too slow.

184
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:52,180
Thanks.

185
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:57,790
[South Lake City No. 3 High School]

186
00:12:57,790 --> 00:12:59,800
Was I slow with my fourth step?

187
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:01,570
What's wrong?

188
00:13:01,570 --> 00:13:03,440
Did you take a liking to him?

189
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:05,420
What do you think of him?

190
00:13:05,420 --> 00:13:06,389
He's a "no" for me.

191
00:13:06,390 --> 00:13:07,830
He's too short.

192
00:13:07,830 --> 00:13:09,440
He won't make it.

193
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:11,669
Besides, there's only one Stefan Holm.

194
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:12,749
All could be geniuses

195
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:14,850
if they could do as he did easily.

196
00:13:14,850 --> 00:13:16,749
It's not unreasonable for me

197
00:13:16,750 --> 00:13:18,720
to say you're an unwanted child.

198
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:21,440
Why would you believe her words?

199
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,920
However,

200
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:27,600
that lady is quite pretty,

201
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:29,810
elegant and dashing.

202
00:13:40,390 --> 00:13:41,860
She's looking at me now.

203
00:13:41,860 --> 00:13:43,410
She's looking at me.

204
00:13:46,550 --> 00:13:49,669
No. 1032, Duan Yu Cheng.

205
00:13:49,670 --> 00:13:54,280
First attempt at 1.88 meters (6'2").

206
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:57,020
Duan Yu Cheng, 179 cm tall.

207
00:13:57,020 --> 00:13:58,079
His idol is

208
00:13:58,080 --> 00:14:00,439
the Swedish high jumper, Stefan Holm, gold medalist

209
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:03,150
in high jump at the Athens Olympic Games.

210
00:14:03,820 --> 00:14:05,420
Making an approach run,

211
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,400
making a cut,

212
00:14:10,130 --> 00:14:11,430
taking off,

213
00:14:11,430 --> 00:14:12,749
jumping backward over the bar.

214
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:13,860
Success in one go.

215
00:14:13,860 --> 00:14:15,240
He's smart.

216
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:17,210
Did you see that?

217
00:14:17,210 --> 00:14:19,840
He did it right after I told him once.

218
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:28,850
Did I do it right?

219
00:14:32,810 --> 00:14:33,940
Yes, you did.

220
00:14:33,940 --> 00:14:35,320
Thank you.

221
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:38,789
No way.

222
00:14:38,790 --> 00:14:40,710
This child won't make it.

223
00:15:48,630 --> 00:15:50,239
The one you took a liking to

224
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:53,030
failed his last two attempts. Just forget him.

225
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:57,240
There's a third attempt, right? What's the rush?

226
00:16:00,510 --> 00:16:04,290
Duan Yu Cheng, you can do it!

227
00:16:04,290 --> 00:16:07,930
Duan Yu Cheng, you've got this!

228
00:16:07,930 --> 00:16:11,550
Duan Yu Cheng, go for it!

229
00:16:16,790 --> 00:16:19,319
Next, the crossbar will be raised by 2 cm.

230
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:20,860
It is now 2.36 m (7'9").

231
00:16:20,860 --> 00:16:23,990
Currently, only two athletes are left:

232
00:16:23,990 --> 00:16:26,059
Jaroslav Bába from the Czech Republic

233
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:28,059
and two-time champion of World Indoor Championships,

234
00:16:28,060 --> 00:16:30,670
Stefan Holm from Sweden.

235
00:16:30,670 --> 00:16:33,029
Jaroslav Bába is 1.96 m (6'5") tall.

236
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:35,269
He's 15 cm taller than Holm.

237
00:16:35,270 --> 00:16:37,830
Holm will make the first attempt

238
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:41,269
at 2.36 m. A gap of 55 cm is

239
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:43,370
between him and the crossbar.

240
00:16:43,370 --> 00:16:47,050
It's a new height he never conquered before.

241
00:16:47,050 --> 00:16:48,240
That width,

242
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,629
rhythm, and explosive strength!

243
00:16:49,630 --> 00:16:50,819
Holm accelerates,

244
00:16:50,820 --> 00:16:52,629
getting into his rhythm, and widening his width.

245
00:16:52,630 --> 00:16:54,180
He lifts off!

246
00:16:58,540 --> 00:16:59,819
Success in one go!

247
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:02,579
Holm created a miracle in the Olympic Games.

248
00:17:02,580 --> 00:17:04,099
A prodigy 1.81 m (5'11") tall

249
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:06,269
- Hooray!
- in high jump.

250
00:17:06,270 --> 00:17:08,580
He leaped through the sky.

251
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:15,000
Were you shocked?

252
00:17:28,860 --> 00:17:31,380
He's very focused on the field.

253
00:17:31,380 --> 00:17:32,779
He's smart too.

254
00:17:32,780 --> 00:17:35,170
He improved his fourth step again.

255
00:17:35,780 --> 00:17:36,960
Is one's intelligence

256
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:39,130
more important than the bar height?

257
00:17:40,950 --> 00:17:41,611
Are you done?

258
00:17:41,611 --> 00:17:42,680
I guess I'm done here.

259
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:44,610
- We aren't done yet.
- Get here.

260
00:17:46,130 --> 00:17:48,230
It's not like others can't do it.

261
00:17:48,230 --> 00:17:50,980
It's just 1.92 m (6'4"). What are you so proud of?

262
00:17:56,820 --> 00:17:58,710
That lady is leaving.

263
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:02,680
Next jump, 1.95 m (6'5").

264
00:18:04,670 --> 00:18:07,619
Before this, he had a high success rate on all his third attempts.

265
00:18:07,620 --> 00:18:09,540
That means he has a good psychological quality.

266
00:18:09,540 --> 00:18:10,709
No need to study that percentage

267
00:18:10,710 --> 00:18:12,539
if he passed his first attempt.

268
00:18:12,540 --> 00:18:13,890
It's 1.95 m now.

269
00:18:13,890 --> 00:18:15,790
He can't make it. Forget about him.

270
00:18:15,790 --> 00:18:17,470
Director Wang.

271
00:18:17,470 --> 00:18:18,429
How was it?

272
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:19,539
I have a question.

273
00:18:19,540 --> 00:18:20,709
Liu Shan from the high jump event,

274
00:18:20,710 --> 00:18:22,790
is he trying to get into South Lake University?

275
00:18:22,790 --> 00:18:24,450
Normal (Educators) University wanted to recruit him, too.

276
00:18:24,450 --> 00:18:26,410
But he wants to wait for Sports University's enrollment.

277
00:18:26,410 --> 00:18:27,780
He's so near-sighted.

278
00:18:27,780 --> 00:18:30,760
South Lake University's high jump dept. isn't inferior to Sports University's.

279
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:33,750
Maybe he likes the atmosphere there better.

280
00:18:33,750 --> 00:18:34,960
Although that's the case,

281
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:36,830
the competition there is bigger too.

282
00:18:36,830 --> 00:18:38,379
Over twenty people

283
00:18:38,380 --> 00:18:39,909
are as tall as him at Sports University.

284
00:18:39,910 --> 00:18:41,940
- He won't be selected.
- True.

285
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:43,379
He's an ignorant child.

286
00:18:43,380 --> 00:18:45,340
You must talk some sense into him.

287
00:18:52,910 --> 00:18:54,940
He did succeed.

288
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:58,170
That child is good,

289
00:18:58,170 --> 00:19:01,100
but he's too short.

290
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:03,280
Stop wasting your time on him.

291
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:04,749
We're almost done here.

292
00:19:04,750 --> 00:19:06,339
You can look around a little more.

293
00:19:06,340 --> 00:19:07,709
Let's head back after checking out

294
00:19:07,710 --> 00:19:08,859
the 100-meter sprint.

295
00:19:08,860 --> 00:19:09,480
All right.

296
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:11,280
Come on, Xiao Liu, let me tell you something.

297
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:13,579
Talk to Liu Shan.

298
00:19:13,580 --> 00:19:14,539
Okay.

299
00:19:14,540 --> 00:19:16,910
I think South Lake University is...

300
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:52,700
[Duan Yu Cheng]

301
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:54,600
He looks like me.

302
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:57,100
Don't worry.

303
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:59,000
I saw nothing.

304
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:03,200
Miss Sunglasses,

305
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:05,200
are you a coach from South Lake University?

306
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,400
I thought you said you saw nothing.

307
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,800
Are you here to recruit potential athletes?

308
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:13,000
Do you want someone from track and field?

309
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,800
What about high jump?

310
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,400
What do you think about me?

311
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:26,300
You shouldn't have cold food after exercising.

312
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:28,000
I know that. It's not for me.

313
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,600
It's for you.

314
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:32,400
Thank you for guiding me today.

315
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:38,600
Do you not like strawberries?

316
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:44,300
Thanks.

317
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:45,700
Don't mention it.

318
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:51,600
Did you see me clear the mark of 1.95 m?

319
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:53,100
I didn't.

320
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:57,000
What a shame.

321
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,000
It's as if God was helping me today.

322
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,300
Before, when I did takeoff,

323
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,700
my coach always said I did it wrong.

324
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:02,800
But I couldn't change my angle.

325
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:06,400
When you told me to quicken the fourth step,

326
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:08,600
I followed your instructions.

327
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:13,000
After that, I cleared the mark of 1.95 m.

328
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,700
You shouldn't deplete your energy blindly.

329
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:16,200
You have great explosive strength.

330
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:20,200
You can do better if you stabilize your footsteps.

331
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,400
What's the matter?

332
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:31,200
You're indeed a South Lake University coach.

333
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:35,500
You guys are here to recruit students, right?

334
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:37,700
Did you set your eyes on Liu Shan?

335
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,800
I'm not sure about that.

336
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:45,200
I'm not the one in charge of recruiting.

337
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:47,300
Just focus on your competition.

338
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:51,800
You guys did pick Liu Shan, right?

339
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:54,300
Who would you guys pick?

340
00:21:54,300 --> 00:21:55,900
Who would you pick?

341
00:21:57,400 --> 00:22:00,000
Height isn't the only factor we consider.

342
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:03,400
We have to consider many factors.

343
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,700
So it wasn't due to my height?

344
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:09,600
No.

345
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:18,700
Do you know what expression you're showing right now?

346
00:22:18,700 --> 00:22:20,600
You lied.

347
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:22,800
It's fine even if you tell me

348
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:24,600
it is my height.

349
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:26,500
I'm used to it.

350
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:32,600
Athletes for the 100-meter finals,

351
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,900
please report to the check-in counter.

352
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:36,000
Athletes for the 100-meter finals...

353
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:38,600
You still have 100-meter finals. You should go.

354
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:40,800
Do you even know that?

355
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:43,000
Seems you're keeping an eye on me.

356
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:48,000
All right then.

357
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,700
I'll head to the finals now.

358
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,600
I'll dump this for you.

359
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,800
Goodbye.

360
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:02,500
What now?

361
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:04,500
It's nothing. Don't move.

362
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:19,800
♫ Love blinds ♫

363
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:25,300
♫ But I'd rather see the world with these eyes ♫

364
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:26,400
So this is what you look like.

365
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:34,300
♫ What is sacred in this vision of sight is everything ♫

366
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:35,900
Sorry about that.

367
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:40,500
I'll head to the finals now.

368
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:47,600
♫ I'll hide in the light if only ♫

369
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:49,300
Miss Sunglasses,

370
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,800
my first choice is South Lake University!

371
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:56,200
I've remembered your face!

372
00:23:56,200 --> 00:24:00,200
I'll find you in track and field instantly when I enter South Lake University.

373
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:03,600
I'll go there if you guys want me or not.

374
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:07,800
I'll surely be there!

375
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:24,800
[South Lake University]

376
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:29,820
[South Lake University, Staff Dorm]

377
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:14,400
[Senior Brother]

378
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:18,000
Senior Brother.

379
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,700
- You're back?
- Yes.

380
00:25:20,500 --> 00:25:22,400
Are you working out?

381
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:24,500
Come down and have some ice jelly.

382
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:46,500
[Wu Ze, South Lake University Sprint Team Coach]

383
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:52,000
Swing your arms!

384
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:54,200
Do you use your arms to breathe?

385
00:25:55,100 --> 00:25:56,800
You must be out of your mind.

386
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:59,000
Why are you scaring them?

387
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:03,000
Why did he join this team when he's this skinny?

388
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,800
Do you think everyone is from the track and field team

389
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:07,000
or the sprint team?

390
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,400
Goodness.

391
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,000
Seems they aren't training for the 100-meter race;

392
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:12,100
they can't even jog.

393
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:15,300
Are you reproaching me?

394
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:18,600
You know that's not what I mean.

395
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:26,300
What's the best height for a 100-meter sprinter?

396
00:26:26,300 --> 00:26:28,200
For international competitions, it's about 1.9 m (6'3").

397
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:29,400
For local competitions,

398
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:31,400
it's about 1.80 m to 1.85 m (5'11").

399
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:34,600
Usain Bolt is over 1.95 m tall, right?

400
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:36,700
He's an exception.

401
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:38,300
What about Su Bing Tian?

402
00:26:38,300 --> 00:26:40,200
He's an exception, too.

403
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:45,200
Although there are exceptions,

404
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:46,800
one mustn't be shorter or taller than the required height.

405
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:48,400
If you're too tall, your strides are slow.

406
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:50,800
If you're too short, your strides are too short.

407
00:26:54,500 --> 00:26:56,000
I met a guy at South Lake No. 3 High School

408
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:58,800
who was quite good at high jump.

409
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:00,300
He's just too short.

410
00:27:00,300 --> 00:27:02,400
- Old Wang didn't take a liking to him, right?
- Yes.

411
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,800
Stop looking for trouble.

412
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:11,000
You should cherish the free days you have

413
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:14,000
as a postgrad student before you graduate from your studies.

414
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:16,000
Once you become an official coach here,

415
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:17,600
you'll have lots of youngsters to worry about.

416
00:27:17,600 --> 00:27:20,000
I have too much free time on my hands.

417
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:23,000
I'm so bored. I run errands every day.

418
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:25,200
Even if you wish to recruit, you can't do it casually

419
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:26,900
after seeing him perform in one competition.

420
00:27:26,900 --> 00:27:29,400
It's so difficult to meet

421
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:31,100
an athlete who clicks with you

422
00:27:31,100 --> 00:27:33,000
and is fully committed.

423
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:36,100
Many people can never find someone like that.

424
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:40,800
This is a warning.

425
00:27:41,600 --> 00:27:43,400
Even if you do meet someone like that one day,

426
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:46,300
don't offer all you have to that relationship.

427
00:27:46,300 --> 00:27:47,400
Sometimes,

428
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:50,000
it becomes misfortune when things go wrong.

429
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:55,000
Did you remember that?

430
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:58,200
The sports industry is too cruel.

431
00:28:01,700 --> 00:28:05,500
[It's 19 days until Gaokao (university entrance exams).]

432
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:11,400
After my retirement,

433
00:28:11,400 --> 00:28:12,200
I became a postgraduate student

434
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:14,000
in the Faculty of Athletic Training at South Lake University.

435
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:16,500
I aspired to become an excellent coach.
[Postgraduate Thesis]

436
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:19,200
As my father was a renowned track and field coach,

437
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:20,500
I always thought
[Jump]

438
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:22,600
I inherited some of his skills

439
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:24,400
when it came to being a coach.

440
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:25,400
However...

441
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:28,700
Luo Na, bring the javelins to the stadium.

442
00:28:29,700 --> 00:28:30,700
Being an assistant coach

443
00:28:30,700 --> 00:28:32,700
is a side character of the track and field team.

444
00:28:32,700 --> 00:28:35,800
It gave me no freedom or space to utilize my skills.

445
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:48,600
[It's 19 days until Gaokao.]

446
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:50,300
[It's 0 days until Gaokao.]

447
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:59,800
[South Lake University]

448
00:29:02,050 --> 00:29:05,470
[Welcome, New Students]

449
00:29:18,730 --> 00:29:20,550
[South Lake University]

450
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:42,000
This is yours.

451
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:43,900
Here.

452
00:29:44,900 --> 00:29:46,600
Zhou Qi is on leave. Pass this to him.

453
00:29:46,600 --> 00:29:47,700
Yes, Assistant Coach.

454
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:50,400
You didn't keep your diet during the holiday, right?

455
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:52,400
Director Wang wants to speak with you after training.

456
00:29:52,400 --> 00:29:53,600
Yes, Assistant Coach Luo.

457
00:29:53,600 --> 00:29:54,900
- Luo Na!
- Yes!

458
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:58,600
Where are the new mats I asked for?
[South Lake University]

459
00:29:58,600 --> 00:30:00,200
I'll get them now.

460
00:30:04,800 --> 00:30:06,400
Adjust the distance.

461
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:09,100
Coach Wang, here are the mats.

462
00:30:09,100 --> 00:30:11,400
All right, leave them here.

463
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:20,200
Miss Sunglasses!

464
00:30:24,300 --> 00:30:25,800
It's me!

465
00:30:26,500 --> 00:30:28,200
You're Duan...

466
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:31,400
Wait for me.

467
00:30:39,400 --> 00:30:40,600
Long time no see.

468
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:42,400
What are you doing here?

469
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:43,800
I'm here to enroll.

470
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:45,400
"Enroll"?

471
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:52,000
[Letter of Admission]

472
00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:55,600
[Letter of Admission, Duan Yu Cheng]

473
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:58,000
"School of Economics and Management"?

474
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:00,500
- Are you majoring in finance?
- Yes.

475
00:31:00,500 --> 00:31:03,900
My father said if I can't become an athlete,

476
00:31:03,900 --> 00:31:06,800
I should get into this university by majoring in something promising.

477
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:09,200
You're something else.

478
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:10,800
You make South Lake University's top program

479
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:13,600
sound like a piece of cake.

480
00:31:14,900 --> 00:31:16,300
Amazing.

481
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:18,900
I guess I'm not too bad.

482
00:31:18,900 --> 00:31:21,600
I did spend many sleepless nights studying.

483
00:31:21,600 --> 00:31:23,100
You're awesome.

484
00:31:23,100 --> 00:31:24,200
Keep up the good work.

485
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:26,400
You have a bright future ahead.

486
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:28,100
Are you leaving already?

487
00:31:28,100 --> 00:31:29,700
What else should I do?

488
00:31:30,500 --> 00:31:32,700
Did you forget what I said?

489
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:40,500
Do you recall them now?

490
00:31:40,500 --> 00:31:41,800
I do.

491
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:45,500
If so, let me join the track and field team, Miss Sunglasses.

492
00:31:45,500 --> 00:31:48,300
First, my last name is Luo.

493
00:31:48,300 --> 00:31:50,200
I'm a postgraduate student of Sports Faculty.

494
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:52,200
I'm an assistant coach of the track and field team.

495
00:31:52,200 --> 00:31:55,200
You can call me Ms. Luo or Coach Luo.

496
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:58,600
Do not call me Miss Sunglasses.

497
00:31:58,600 --> 00:32:00,600
All right, Coach Luo.

498
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:02,700
May I join the track and field team?

499
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:06,300
You can continue to practice high jump if you wish.

500
00:32:06,300 --> 00:32:07,700
We have the high jump society.

501
00:32:07,700 --> 00:32:09,000
They have professional coaches.

502
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:11,000
You can join them.

503
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:13,000
I don't wish to join a society.

504
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:14,900
I want to join the track and field team.

505
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:18,600
Economics and Management has a busy study schedule.

506
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:21,000
You won't have time to train.

507
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:22,000
You entered with much effort.

508
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:23,800
You should keep up the good work.

509
00:32:25,300 --> 00:32:26,900
I grew taller

510
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:30,000
by 3 cm (1.2 inches).

511
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:32,400
I'm 1.82 m (5'11.7") tall now.

512
00:32:34,300 --> 00:32:38,200
I will balance my training and my studies.

513
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:40,400
I can show you my grades.

514
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:41,800
If I do well in my grades,

515
00:32:41,800 --> 00:32:45,400
let me join the field and track team, okay?

516
00:32:46,500 --> 00:32:47,400
Fine.

517
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:48,800
You can give it a try by then.

518
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:50,800
We would like to have

519
00:32:50,800 --> 00:32:54,100
more top-quality athletes as well.

520
00:32:54,100 --> 00:32:55,400
All right.

521
00:32:56,100 --> 00:32:57,400
I'll go and enroll now.

522
00:32:57,400 --> 00:32:58,800
Go ahead.

523
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:05,800
Can't you take the proper entrance?

524
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:10,800
Okay, I'll come down now.

525
00:33:10,800 --> 00:33:11,800
Forget it.

526
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:13,400
Just go.

527
00:33:16,800 --> 00:33:18,500
See you then.

528
00:33:18,500 --> 00:33:20,000
See you later, Miss Sunglasses.

529
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:21,800
It's "Coach" for you.

530
00:33:40,600 --> 00:33:41,900
Come in.

531
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:45,000
Is this Dorm 117?

532
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:46,200
Hello, Bro.

533
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:47,200
Hello.

534
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:48,600
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

535
00:33:48,600 --> 00:33:49,700
Hu Jun Xiao.

536
00:33:49,700 --> 00:33:51,100
Hu Jun Xiao!

537
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:53,000
He's asleep.

538
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:54,800
It's fine.

539
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:58,600
- We're in the same faculty, right?
- Yes.

540
00:33:58,600 --> 00:34:00,300
How should I address you all?

541
00:34:00,300 --> 00:34:02,790
I'm Jia Shi Li. You can call me Old Jia.

542
00:34:02,790 --> 00:34:04,419
"Old Jia"? Okay.

543
00:34:04,419 --> 00:34:05,800
He's Han Dai.

544
00:34:05,800 --> 00:34:08,200
His idol is...

545
00:34:08,200 --> 00:34:09,400
that guy...

546
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:10,800
